author: gstein
msg: Switch the working file installation for another case in the update
process. But we also have to be wary of major ugliness around file
externals, which appear to be placing the database into an improper state
(merge_file): take an INSTALL_FROM parameter to indicate where the
working copy file install (ref: INSTALL_PRISTINE) will occur from. use
this new install process for another scenario, but be wary of file
externals, which are (currently) monkeyed up from a database standpoint.
(close_file): pass INSTALL_FROM to merge_file, and use it for the
working copy file install process. we can't clean the file up just
yet, since it may refer to the revert base, but future conditions
should be able to do the removal.
